Description: Sherd of base and floor of North Ionian pottery open vase, probably plate; grooved underneath; raised moulding around centre on inside; white slip. Underside reserved, though with depositional stains; red dipinto. Inside: moulding and centre glazed, surrounded by frieze of maeanders, triglyphs and hollow squares; trace of perhaps animal frieze preserved to the outside.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Aphrodite (Naukratis) (noted on Gardner's plate)
Curator's comments: In pencil on floor 'List 33' and '915', struck through. Probably from same large plate, minimum diameter36 cm, as1965,0930.496 and 497.
